-- Zijin Mining's Waste Leak Has `Substantial Effect' on Copper Production
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-12T12:35:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/zijin-mining-s-waste-leak-has-substantial-effect-on-copper-production.html

          
          
              Zijin Mining Group Co. has
suspended stockpiling of ore at the Zijinshan mine after waste
water containing acidic copper leaked into a nearby river, the
company said in a statement to the Hong Kong stock exchange
today. The incident has had a “substantial effect” on copper
production at the mine, it said.  
 The company’s shares were suspended today and will resume
trading tomorrow, July 13, it said.  
          
          


  


        